    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1995) - DIAGNOSTIC TOOLS - Pro-Link 9000 Electronic Service tool
        Operation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Pro-Link 9000 Electronic Service tool Operation</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
            <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
            <para>Fault codes can be detected and stored in three components. The IDM (Injector Driver Module), the ECM
                (Electronic Control Module), and the VPM (Vehicle Personality Module).
            </para>
            <para>The EST (Electronic Service Tool)
                <emph type="bold">(Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e145_199.xml" xrefid="ef1450522">5.22</hotlnk>)
                </emph>
                is used to access stored fault codes by plugging it into the American Trucking Association (ATA) data
                link connector located in the cab of the vehicle. This allows the tool to communicate with the VPM and
                gather faults from the ECM and IDM through the VPM.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
